Quote:  <i>Senecio reinoldii</i> MUTTONBIRD SCRUB <i>... Puuheretaaiko ... Muttonwood ... Shrub or small tree. Leaves leathery ... </i>The term `muttonbird scrub' is often used generally for coastal scrub dominated by any of the

tree daisies [<i>Olearia</i> and <i>Senecio</i> spp.], frequently mixed with inaka.
